## Remarks  
 <span data-ttu-id="5cc87-102">Windows Desktop Speech のコレクションとして認識される語句を返します<xref:System.Speech.Recognition.RecognizedWordUnit>または<xref:System.Speech.Recognition.ReplacementText>オブジェクト。</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="5cc87-102">Windows Desktop Speech returns recognized phrases as collections of <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.RecognizedWordUnit> or <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.ReplacementText> objects.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="5cc87-103">各オブジェクトは、1 つの単語または句読点に対応します。</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="5cc87-103">Each object corresponds to a single word or punctuation mark.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="5cc87-104">`DisplayAttributes`のプロパティを<xref:System.Speech.Recognition.RecognizedWordUnit>または<xref:System.Speech.Recognition.ReplacementText>のメンバーを使用して、<xref:System.Speech.Recognition.DisplayAttributes>を印刷する方法の間隔を表す列挙体は、特定の単語または句読点を囲む処理されます。</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="5cc87-104">The `DisplayAttributes` property of a <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.RecognizedWordUnit> or <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.ReplacementText> uses a member of the <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.DisplayAttributes> enumeration to describe how print spacing is handled around a given word or punctuation mark.</span></span>  
  
 <span data-ttu-id="5cc87-105">2 つ以上のメンバー、`DisplayAttributes`積によって列挙体を組み合わせることができます`OR`を特定のワードの表示方法を指定します。</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="5cc87-105">Two or more members of the `DisplayAttributes` enumeration may be combined by a bit-wise `OR` to specify how a particular word should be displayed.</span></span>  
  
> [!NOTE]
>  <span data-ttu-id="5cc87-106">音声認識エンジンを使用する書式設定の表示は、特定の言語です。</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="5cc87-106">The display formatting that the speech recognizer uses is language specific.</span></span>  
  
 <span data-ttu-id="5cc87-107">たとえば、によって提供される既定のシステム文法を使用する認識エンジンに入力語句<xref:System.Speech.Recognition.DictationGrammar>「こんにちはコンマ言いました期間」です。</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="5cc87-107">For example, suppose the input phrase to a recognition engine using the default system grammar provided by <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.DictationGrammar> is "Hello comma he said period".</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="5cc87-108">認識エンジンから返されます、 <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.RecognizedPhrase> 5 つ含む<xref:System.Speech.Recognition.RecognizedWordUnit>次のように、次を含むオブジェクトが文字列`DisplayAttributes`値。</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="5cc87-108">Then the recognition engine returns a <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.RecognizedPhrase> containing five <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.RecognizedWordUnit> objects containing the following strings with the following `DisplayAttributes` values.</span></span>  
  
|<span data-ttu-id="5cc87-109">アイテム</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="5cc87-109">Item</span></span>|`DisplayAttributes`|  
|----------|-------------------------|  
|<span data-ttu-id="5cc87-110">こんにちは</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="5cc87-110">Hello</span></span>|<span data-ttu-id="5cc87-111">OneTrailingSpace</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="5cc87-111">OneTrailingSpace</span></span>|  
|<span data-ttu-id="5cc87-112">,</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="5cc87-112">,</span></span>|<span data-ttu-id="5cc87-113">OneTrailingSpace &#124; ConsumeLeadingSpaces</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="5cc87-113">OneTrailingSpace &#124; ConsumeLeadingSpaces</span></span>|  
|<span data-ttu-id="5cc87-114">he</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="5cc87-114">he</span></span>|<span data-ttu-id="5cc87-115">OneTrailingSpace</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="5cc87-115">OneTrailingSpace</span></span>|  
|<span data-ttu-id="5cc87-116">ただし</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="5cc87-116">said</span></span>|<span data-ttu-id="5cc87-117">OneTrailingSpace</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="5cc87-117">OneTrailingSpace</span></span>|  
|<span data-ttu-id="5cc87-118">である必要があります。</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="5cc87-118">.</span></span>|<span data-ttu-id="5cc87-119">OneTrailingSpace &#124; ConsumeLeadingSpaces</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="5cc87-119">OneTrailingSpace &#124; ConsumeLeadingSpaces</span></span>|  
  
 <span data-ttu-id="5cc87-120">この認識された語句として印刷に返されるテキスト:「こんにちは、言いました」。</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="5cc87-120">The text returned for this recognized phrase is printed as: "Hello, he said."</span></span>  
  
   
  
## Examples  
 <span data-ttu-id="5cc87-121">次の例では、<xref:System.Speech.Recognition.RecognizedWordUnit.DisplayAttributes%2A>プロパティの一覧の<xref:System.Speech.Recognition.RecognizedWordUnit>句として、単語を書式設定するオブジェクト。</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="5cc87-121">The following example uses the <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.RecognizedWordUnit.DisplayAttributes%2A> property of a list of <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.RecognizedWordUnit> objects to format the words as a phrase.</span></span>  
  
```csharp  
  
// Use the DisplayAttributes property to format speech as text.   
  
static string GetDisplayText(List<RecognizedWordUnit> words)  
{  
  StringBuilder sb = new StringBuilder();  
  
  // Concatenate the word units together. Use the DisplayAttributes  
  // property of each word unit to add or remove white space around  
  // the word unit.  
  foreach (RecognizedWordUnit word in words)  
  {  
    if ((word.DisplayAttributes  
      & DisplayAttributes.ConsumeLeadingSpaces) != 0))  
    {  
      sb = new StringBuilder(sb.ToString().TrimEnd());  
    }  
  
    sb.Append(word.Text);  
  
    if ((word.DisplayAttributes  
      & DisplayAttributes.OneTrailingSpace) != 0)  
    {  
      sb.Append(" ");  
    }  
    else if ((word.DisplayAttributes  
      & DisplayAttributes.TwoTrailingSpaces) != 0)  
    {  
      sb.Append("  ");  
    }  
  }  
  
  return sb.ToString();  
}  
  
```
